  "doc_id": "9698",
  "text": "Two fields in particular are useful to our proposal: the RTP [CITATION_1] timestamp field that carries information about the current session clock of the VoIP call, and the NTP timestamp field that carries information about the local 'wall clock' time that corresponds to the session clock. The VoIP session clock is a counter increased with every sample taken by the codec. Typically codecs sample the audio signal at a fixed rate (e.g. 8 kHz for G711), and the timestamp included in the RTP header reflects the sampling instant of the first byte in that RTP packet.",
  "correct_citation": {
